Linux File System Overview

Linux ka file system ek tree structure hai jisme root directory "/" hoti hai. 
Sabhi files aur directories isi root ke andar hoti hain.

Important directories:
- /home : User directories
- /bin  : Basic commands
- /etc  : Configuration files
- /var  : Logs aur variable data
- /tmp  : Temporary files
- /dev  : Device files
- /proc : System aur process information
- /root : Root user ka home directory

Absolute path: /etc/hosts
Relative path: ./file.txt

